42 bool Constant::isNegativeZeroValue() const { 0
43 // Floating point values have an explicit -0.0 value. ----
44 if (const ConstantFP *CFP = dyn_cast(this)) 0
45 return CFP->isZero() && CFP->isNegative(); 0
46 ----
47 // Equivalent for a vector of -0.0's. ----
48 if (getType()->isVectorTy()) 0
49 if (const auto *SplatCFP = dyn_cast_or_null(getSplatValue())) 0
50 return SplatCFP->isNegativeZeroValue(); 0
51 ----
52 // We've already handled true FP case; any other FP vectors can't represent -0.0. ----
53 if (getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) 0
54 return false; 0
55 ----
56 // Otherwise, just use +0.0. ----
57 return isNullValue(); 0
58 } ----

76 bool Constant::isNullValue() const { 0
77 // 0 is null. ----
78 if (const ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast(this)) 0
79 return CI->isZero(); 0
80 ----
81 // +0.0 is null. ----
82 if (const ConstantFP *CFP = dyn_cast(this)) 0
83 // ppc_fp128 determine isZero using high order double only ----
84 // Should check the bitwise value to make sure all bits are zero. ----
85 return CFP->isExactlyValue(+0.0); 0
86 ----
87 // constant zero is zero for aggregates, cpnull is null for pointers, none for ----
88 // tokens. ----
89 return isa(this) || isa(this) || 0
90 isa(this) || isa(this); 0
91 } ----

284 bool Constant::isElementWiseEqual(Value *Y) const { 0
285 // Are they fully identical? ----
286 if (this == Y) 0
287 return true; 0
288 ----
289 // The input value must be a vector constant with the same type. ----
290 auto *VTy = dyn_cast(getType()); 0
291 if (!isa(Y) || !VTy || VTy != Y->getType()) 0
292 return false; 0
293 ----
294 // TODO: Compare pointer constants? ----
295 if (!(VTy->getElementType()->isIntegerTy() || 0
296 VTy->getElementType()->isFloatingPointTy())) 0
297 return false; 0
298 ----
299 // They may still be identical element-wise (if they have `undef`s). ----
300 // Bitcast to integer to allow exact bitwise comparison for all types. ----
301 Type *IntTy = VectorType::getInteger(VTy); 0
302 Constant *C0 = ConstantExpr::getBitCast(const_cast(this), IntTy); 0
303 Constant *C1 = ConstantExpr::getBitCast(cast(Y), IntTy); 0
304 Constant *CmpEq = ConstantExpr::getICmp(ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ, C0, C1); 0
305 return isa(CmpEq) || match(CmpEq, m_One()); 0
306 } ----

311 if (auto *VTy = dyn_cast(C->getType())) { 0

320 i != e; ++i) { 0
321 if (Constant *Elem = C->getAggregateElement(i)) 0
322 if (HasFn(Elem)) 0
323 return true; 0

325 } ----

386 Constant *Constant::getIntegerValue(Type *Ty, const APInt &V) { 0
387 Type *ScalarTy = Ty->getScalarType(); 0
388 ----
389 // Create the base integer constant. ----
390 Constant *C = ConstantInt::get(Ty->getContext(), V); 0
391 ----
392 // Convert an integer to a pointer, if necessary. ----
393 if (PointerType *PTy = dyn_cast(ScalarTy)) 0
394 C = ConstantExpr::getIntToPtr(C, PTy); 0
395 ----
396 // Broadcast a scalar to a vector, if necessary. ----
397 if (VectorType *VTy = dyn_cast(Ty)) 0
398 C = ConstantVector::getSplat(VTy->getElementCount(), C); 0
399 ----
400 return C; 0
401 } ----

410 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), FL); 0

418 Constant *Constant::getAggregateElement(unsigned Elt) const { 0
419 assert((getType()->isAggregateType() || getType()->isVectorTy()) && 0
420 "Must be an aggregate/vector constant"); ----
421 ----
422 if (const auto *CC = dyn_cast(this)) 0
423 return Elt < CC->getNumOperands() ? CC->getOperand(Elt) : nullptr; 0
424 ----
425 if (const auto *CAZ = dyn_cast(this)) 0
426 return Elt < CAZ->getElementCount().getKnownMinValue() 0
427 ? CAZ->getElementValue(Elt) 0
428 : nullptr; 0
429 ----
430 // FIXME: getNumElements() will fail for non-fixed vector types. ----
431 if (isa(getType())) 0
432 return nullptr; 0
433 ----
434 if (const auto *PV = dyn_cast(this)) 0
435 return Elt < PV->getNumElements() ? PV->getElementValue(Elt) : nullptr; 0
436 ----
437 if (const auto *UV = dyn_cast(this)) 0
438 return Elt < UV->getNumElements() ? UV->getElementValue(Elt) : nullptr; 0
439 ----
440 if (const auto *CDS = dyn_cast(this)) 0
441 return Elt < CDS->getNumElements() ? CDS->getElementAsConstant(Elt) 0
442 : nullptr; 0
443 ----
444 return nullptr; 0
445 } ----

447 Constant *Constant::getAggregateElement(Constant *Elt) const { 0
448 assert(isa(Elt->getType()) && "Index must be an integer"); 0
449 if (ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast(Elt)) { 0
450 // Check if the constant fits into an uint64_t. ----
451 if (CI->getValue().getActiveBits() > 64) 0
452 return nullptr; 0
453 return getAggregateElement(CI->getZExtValue()); 0
454 } ----
455 return nullptr; 0
456 } ----

458 void Constant::destroyConstant() { 0
459 /// First call destroyConstantImpl on the subclass. This gives the subclass ----
460 /// a chance to remove the constant from any maps/pools it's contained in. ----
461 switch (getValueID()) { 0
462 default: 0
463 llvm_unreachable("Not a constant!"); 0
464 #define HANDLE_CONSTANT(Name) \ ----
465 case Value::Name##Val: \ ----
466 cast(this)->destroyConstantImpl(); \ ----
467 break; ----
468 #include "llvm/IR/Value.def" ----
469 } ----
470 ----
471 // When a Constant is destroyed, there may be lingering ----
472 // references to the constant by other constants in the constant pool. These ----
473 // constants are implicitly dependent on the module that is being deleted, ----
474 // but they don't know that. Because we only find out when the CPV is ----
475 // deleted, we must now notify all of our users (that should only be ----
476 // Constants) that they are, in fact, invalid now and should be deleted. ----
477 // ----
478 while (!use_empty()) { 0
479 Value *V = user_back(); 0
480 #ifndef NDEBUG // Only in -g mode... ----
481 if (!isa(V)) { 0
482 dbgs() << "While deleting: " << *this 0
483 << "\n\nUse still stuck around after Def is destroyed: " << *V 0
484 << "\n\n"; 0
485 } ----
486 #endif ----
487 assert(isa(V) && "References remain to Constant being destroyed"); 0
488 cast(V)->destroyConstant(); 0
489 ----
490 // The constant should remove itself from our use list... ----
491 assert((use_empty() || user_back() != V) && "Constant not removed!"); 0
492 } ----
493 ----
494 // Value has no outstanding references it is safe to delete it now... ----
495 deleteConstant(this); 0
496 } 0

499 switch (C->getValueID()) { 0
500 case Constant::ConstantIntVal: 0
501 delete static_cast(C); 0
502 break; 0
503 case Constant::ConstantFPVal: 0
504 delete static_cast(C); 0
505 break; 0
506 case Constant::ConstantAggregateZeroVal: 0
507 delete static_cast(C); 0
508 break; 0
509 case Constant::ConstantArrayVal: 0
510 delete static_cast(C); 0
511 break; 0
512 case Constant::ConstantStructVal: 0
513 delete static_cast(C); 0
514 break; 0
515 case Constant::ConstantVectorVal: 0
516 delete static_cast(C); 0
517 break; 0
518 case Constant::ConstantPointerNullVal: 0
519 delete static_cast(C); 0
520 break; 0
521 case Constant::ConstantDataArrayVal: 0
522 delete static_cast(C); 0
523 break; 0
524 case Constant::ConstantDataVectorVal: 0
525 delete static_cast(C); 0
526 break; 0
527 case Constant::ConstantTokenNoneVal: 0
528 delete static_cast(C); 0
529 break; 0
530 case Constant::BlockAddressVal: 0
531 delete static_cast(C); 0
532 break; 0
533 case Constant::DSOLocalEquivalentVal: 0
534 delete static_cast(C); 0
535 break; 0
536 case Constant::NoCFIValueVal: 0
537 delete static_cast(C); 0
538 break; 0
539 case Constant::UndefValueVal: 0
540 delete static_cast(C); 0
541 break; 0
542 case Constant::PoisonValueVal: 0
543 delete static_cast(C); 0
544 break; 0
545 case Constant::ConstantExprVal: 0
546 if (isa(C)) 0
547 delete static_cast(C); 0
548 else if (isa(C)) 0
549 delete static_cast(C); 0
550 else if (isa(C)) 0
551 delete static_cast(C); 0
552 else if (isa(C)) 0
553 delete static_cast(C); 0
554 else if (isa(C)) 0
555 delete static_cast(C); 0
556 else if (isa(C)) 0
557 delete static_cast(C); 0
558 else if (isa(C)) 0
559 delete static_cast(C); 0
560 else ----
561 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected constant expr"); 0
562 break; 0
563 default: 0
564 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected constant"); 0
565 } ----
566 } 0

568 /// Check if C contains a GlobalValue for which Predicate is true. ----
569 static bool ----
570 ConstHasGlobalValuePredicate(const Constant *C, 0
571 bool (*Predicate)(const GlobalValue *)) { ----
572 SmallPtrSet Visited; 0
573 SmallVector WorkList; 0
574 WorkList.push_back(C); 0
575 Visited.insert(C); 0
576 ----
577 while (!WorkList.empty()) { 0
578 const Constant *WorkItem = WorkList.pop_back_val(); 0
579 if (const auto *GV = dyn_cast(WorkItem)) 0
580 if (Predicate(GV)) 0
581 return true; 0
582 for (const Value *Op : WorkItem->operands()) { 0
583 const Constant *ConstOp = dyn_cast(Op); 0
584 if (!ConstOp) 0
585 continue; 0
586 if (Visited.insert(ConstOp).second) 0
587 WorkList.push_back(ConstOp); 0
588 } ----
589 } ----
590 return false; 0
591 } 0

626 ----
627 Constant::PossibleRelocationsTy Constant::getRelocationInfo() const { 0
628 if (isa(this)) 0
629 return GlobalRelocation; // Global reference. 0
630 ----
631 if (const BlockAddress *BA = dyn_cast(this)) 0
632 return BA->getFunction()->getRelocationInfo(); 0
633 ----
634 if (const ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast(this)) { 0
635 if (CE->getOpcode() == Instruction::Sub) { 0
636 ConstantExpr *LHS = dyn_cast(CE->getOperand(0)); 0
637 ConstantExpr *RHS = dyn_cast(CE->getOperand(1)); 0
638 if (LHS && RHS && LHS->getOpcode() == Instruction::PtrToInt && 0
639 RHS->getOpcode() == Instruction::PtrToInt) { 0
640 Constant *LHSOp0 = LHS->getOperand(0); 0
641 Constant *RHSOp0 = RHS->getOperand(0); 0
642 ----
643 // While raw uses of blockaddress need to be relocated, differences ----
644 // between two of them don't when they are for labels in the same ----
645 // function. This is a common idiom when creating a table for the ----
646 // indirect goto extension, so we handle it efficiently here. ----
647 if (isa(LHSOp0) && isa(RHSOp0) && 0
648 cast(LHSOp0)->getFunction() == 0
649 cast(RHSOp0)->getFunction()) 0
650 return NoRelocation; 0
651 ----
652 // Relative pointers do not need to be dynamically relocated. ----
653 if (auto *RHSGV = 0
654 dyn_cast(RHSOp0->stripInBoundsConstantOffsets())) { 0
655 auto *LHS = LHSOp0->stripInBoundsConstantOffsets(); 0
656 if (auto *LHSGV = dyn_cast(LHS)) { 0
657 if (LHSGV->isDSOLocal() && RHSGV->isDSOLocal()) 0
658 return LocalRelocation; 0
659 } else if (isa(LHS)) { 0
660 if (RHSGV->isDSOLocal()) 0
661 return LocalRelocation; 0
662 } ----
663 } ----
664 } ----
665 } ----
666 } ----
667 ----
668 PossibleRelocationsTy Result = NoRelocation; 0
669 for (unsigned i = 0, e = getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) 0
670 Result = 0
671 std::max(cast(getOperand(i))->getRelocationInfo(), Result); 0
672 ----
673 return Result; 0
674 } ----
675 ----
676 /// Return true if the specified constantexpr is dead. This involves ----
677 /// recursively traversing users of the constantexpr. ----
678 /// If RemoveDeadUsers is true, also remove dead users at the same time. ----
679 static bool constantIsDead(const Constant *C, bool RemoveDeadUsers) { 0
680 if (isa(C)) return false; // Cannot remove this 0
681 ----
682 Value::const_user_iterator I = C->user_begin(), E = C->user_end(); 0
683 while (I != E) { 0
684 const Constant *User = dyn_cast(*I); 0
685 if (!User) return false; // Non-constant usage; 0
686 if (!constantIsDead(User, RemoveDeadUsers)) 0
687 return false; // Constant wasn't dead 0
688 ----
689 // Just removed User, so the iterator was invalidated. ----
690 // Since we return immediately upon finding a live user, we can always ----
691 // restart from user_begin(). ----
692 if (RemoveDeadUsers) 0
693 I = C->user_begin(); 0
694 else ----
695 ++I; 0
696 } ----
697 ----
698 if (RemoveDeadUsers) { 0
699 // If C is only used by metadata, it should not be preserved but should ----
700 // have its uses replaced. ----
701 ReplaceableMetadataImpl::SalvageDebugInfo(*C); 0
702 const_cast(C)->destroyConstant(); 0
703 } ----
704 ----
705 return true; 0
706 } ----
707 ----
708 void Constant::removeDeadConstantUsers() const { 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
709 Value::const_user_iterator I = user_begin(), E = user_end(); 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
710 Value::const_user_iterator LastNonDeadUser = E; 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
711 while (I != E) { 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
712 const Constant *User = dyn_cast(*I); 0
713 if (!User) { 0
714 LastNonDeadUser = I; 0
715 ++I; 0
716 continue; 0
717 } ----
718 ----
719 if (!constantIsDead(User, /* RemoveDeadUsers= */ true)) { 0
720 // If the constant wasn't dead, remember that this was the last live use ----
721 // and move on to the next constant. ----
722 LastNonDeadUser = I; 0
723 ++I; 0
724 continue; 0
725 } ----
726 ----
727 // If the constant was dead, then the iterator is invalidated. ----
728 if (LastNonDeadUser == E) 0
729 I = user_begin(); 0
730 else ----
731 I = std::next(LastNonDeadUser); 0
732 } ----
733 } 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
734 ----
735 bool Constant::hasOneLiveUse() const { return hasNLiveUses(1); } 0
736 ----
737 bool Constant::hasZeroLiveUses() const { return hasNLiveUses(0); } 0
738 ----
739 bool Constant::hasNLiveUses(unsigned N) const { 0
740 unsigned NumUses = 0; 0
741 for (const Use &U : uses()) { 0
742 const Constant *User = dyn_cast(U.getUser()); 0
743 if (!User || !constantIsDead(User, /* RemoveDeadUsers= */ false)) { 0
744 ++NumUses; 0
745 ----
746 if (NumUses > N) 0
747 return false; 0
748 } ----
749 } ----
750 return NumUses == N; 0
751 } ----

753 Constant *Constant::replaceUndefsWith(Constant *C, Constant *Replacement) { 0
754 assert(C && Replacement && "Expected non-nullptr constant arguments"); 0
755 Type *Ty = C->getType(); 0
756 if (match(C, m_Undef())) { 0
757 assert(Ty == Replacement->getType() && "Expected matching types"); 0
758 return Replacement; 0
759 } ----
760 ----
761 // Don't know how to deal with this constant. ----
762 auto *VTy = dyn_cast(Ty); 0
763 if (!VTy) 0
764 return C; 0
765 ----
766 unsigned NumElts = VTy->getNumElements(); 0
767 SmallVector NewC(NumElts); 0
768 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) { 0
769 Constant *EltC = C->getAggregateElement(i); 0
770 assert((!EltC || EltC->getType() == Replacement->getType()) && 0
771 "Expected matching types"); ----
772 NewC[i] = EltC && match(EltC, m_Undef()) ? Replacement : EltC; 0
773 } ----
774 return ConstantVector::get(NewC); 0
775 } 0
776 ----
777 Constant *Constant::mergeUndefsWith(Constant *C, Constant *Other) { 0
778 assert(C && Other && "Expected non-nullptr constant arguments"); 0
779 if (match(C, m_Undef())) 0
780 return C; 0
781 ----
782 Type *Ty = C->getType(); 0
783 if (match(Other, m_Undef())) 0
784 return UndefValue::get(Ty); 0
785 ----
786 auto *VTy = dyn_cast(Ty); 0
787 if (!VTy) 0
788 return C; 0
789 ----
790 Type *EltTy = VTy->getElementType(); 0
791 unsigned NumElts = VTy->getNumElements(); 0
792 assert(isa(Other->getType()) && 0
793 cast(Other->getType())->getNumElements() == NumElts && ----
794 "Type mismatch"); ----
795 ----
796 bool FoundExtraUndef = false; 0
797 SmallVector NewC(NumElts); 0
798 for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumElts; ++I) { 0
799 NewC[I] = C->getAggregateElement(I); 0
800 Constant *OtherEltC = Other->getAggregateElement(I); 0
801 assert(NewC[I] && OtherEltC && "Unknown vector element"); 0
802 if (!match(NewC[I], m_Undef()) && match(OtherEltC, m_Undef())) { 0
803 NewC[I] = UndefValue::get(EltTy); 0
804 FoundExtraUndef = true; 0
805 } ----
806 } ----
807 if (FoundExtraUndef) 0
808 return ConstantVector::get(NewC); 0
809 return C; 0
810 } 0
811 ----
812 bool Constant::isManifestConstant() const { 0
813 if (isa(this)) 0
814 return true; 0
815 if (isa(this) || isa(this)) { 0
816 for (const Value *Op : operand_values()) 0
817 if (!cast(Op)->isManifestConstant()) 0
818 return false; 0
819 return true; 0
820 } ----
821 return false; 0
822 } ----

1186 template ----
1187 static Constant *getSequenceIfElementsMatch(Constant *C, 0
1188 ArrayRef V) { ----
1189 // We speculatively build the elements here even if it turns out that there is ----
1190 // a constantexpr or something else weird, since it is so uncommon for that to ----
1191 // happen. ----
1192 if (ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast(C)) { 0
1193 if (CI->getType()->isIntegerTy(8)) 0
1194 return getIntSequenceIfElementsMatch(V); 0
1195 else if (CI->getType()->isIntegerTy(16)) 0
1196 return getIntSequenceIfElementsMatch(V); 0
1197 else if (CI->getType()->isIntegerTy(32)) 0
1198 return getIntSequenceIfElementsMatch(V); 0
1199 else if (CI->getType()->isIntegerTy(64)) 0
1200 return getIntSequenceIfElementsMatch(V); 0
1201 } else if (ConstantFP *CFP = dyn_cast(C)) { 0
1202 if (CFP->getType()->isHalfTy() || CFP->getType()->isBFloatTy()) 0
1203 return getFPSequenceIfElementsMatch(V); 0
1204 else if (CFP->getType()->isFloatTy()) 0
1205 return getFPSequenceIfElementsMatch(V); 0
1206 else if (CFP->getType()->isDoubleTy()) 0
1207 return getFPSequenceIfElementsMatch(V); 0
1208 } ----
1209 ----
1210 return nullptr; 0
1211 } ----

1213 ConstantAggregate::ConstantAggregate(Type *T, ValueTy VT, 0
1214 ArrayRef V) ----

1217 llvm::copy(V, op_begin()); 0

1220 if (auto *ST = dyn_cast(T)) { 0

1223 for (unsigned I = 0, E = V.size(); I != E; ++I) 0

1240 ----
1241 Constant *ConstantArray::getImpl(ArrayType *Ty, ArrayRef V) { 0
1242 // Empty arrays are canonicalized to ConstantAggregateZero. ----
1243 if (V.empty()) 0
1244 return ConstantAggregateZero::get(Ty); 0
1245 ----
1246 for (Constant *C : V) { 0
1247 assert(C->getType() == Ty->getElementType() && 0
1248 "Wrong type in array element initializer"); ----
1249 (void)C; ----
1250 } ----
1251 ----
1252 // If this is an all-zero array, return a ConstantAggregateZero object. If ----
1253 // all undef, return an UndefValue, if "all simple", then return a ----
1254 // ConstantDataArray. ----
1255 Constant *C = V[0]; 0
1256 if (isa(C) && rangeOnlyContains(V.begin(), V.end(), C)) 0
1257 return PoisonValue::get(Ty); 0
1258 ----
1259 if (isa(C) && rangeOnlyContains(V.begin(), V.end(), C)) 0
1260 return UndefValue::get(Ty); 0
1261 ----
1262 if (C->isNullValue() && rangeOnlyContains(V.begin(), V.end(), C)) 0
1263 return ConstantAggregateZero::get(Ty); 0
1264 ----
1265 // Check to see if all of the elements are ConstantFP or ConstantInt and if ----
1266 // the element type is compatible with ConstantDataVector. If so, use it. ----
1267 if (ConstantDataSequential::isElementTypeCompatible(C->getType())) 0
1268 return getSequenceIfElementsMatch(C, V); 0
1269 ----
1270 // Otherwise, we really do want to create a ConstantArray. ----
1271 return nullptr; 0
1272 } ----
1273 ----
1274 StructType *ConstantStruct::getTypeForElements(LLVMContext &Context, 0
1275 ArrayRef V, ----
1276 bool Packed) { ----
1277 unsigned VecSize = V.size(); 0
1278 SmallVector EltTypes(VecSize); 0
1279 for (unsigned i = 0; i != VecSize; ++i) 0
1280 EltTypes[i] = V[i]->getType(); 0
1281 ----
1282 return StructType::get(Context, EltTypes, Packed); 0
1283 } 0
1284 ----
1285 ----
1286 StructType *ConstantStruct::getTypeForElements(ArrayRef V, 0
1287 bool Packed) { ----
1288 assert(!V.empty() && 0
1289 "ConstantStruct::getTypeForElements cannot be called on empty list"); ----
1290 return getTypeForElements(V[0]->getContext(), V, Packed); 0
1291 } ----
1292 ----
1293 ConstantStruct::ConstantStruct(StructType *T, ArrayRef V) 0
1294 : ConstantAggregate(T, ConstantStructVal, V) { 0
1295 assert((T->isOpaque() || V.size() == T->getNumElements()) && 0
1296 "Invalid initializer for constant struct"); ----
1297 } 0
1298 ----
1299 // ConstantStruct accessors. ----
1300 Constant *ConstantStruct::get(StructType *ST, ArrayRef V) { 0
1301 assert((ST->isOpaque() || ST->getNumElements() == V.size()) && 0
1302 "Incorrect # elements specified to ConstantStruct::get"); ----
1303 ----
1304 // Create a ConstantAggregateZero value if all elements are zeros. ----
1305 bool isZero = true; 0
1306 bool isUndef = false; 0
1307 bool isPoison = false; 0
1308 ----
1309 if (!V.empty()) { 0
1310 isUndef = isa(V[0]); 0
1311 isPoison = isa(V[0]); 0
1312 isZero = V[0]->isNullValue(); 0
1313 // PoisonValue inherits UndefValue, so its check is not necessary. ----
1314 if (isUndef || isZero) { 0
1315 for (Constant *C : V) { 0
1316 if (!C->isNullValue()) 0
1317 isZero = false; 0
1318 if (!isa(C)) 0
1319 isPoison = false; 0
1320 if (isa(C) || !isa(C)) 0
1321 isUndef = false; 0
1322 } ----
1323 } ----
1324 } ----
1325 if (isZero) 0
1326 return ConstantAggregateZero::get(ST); 0
1327 if (isPoison) 0
1328 return PoisonValue::get(ST); 0
1329 if (isUndef) 0
1330 return UndefValue::get(ST); 0
1331 ----
1332 return ST->getContext().pImpl->StructConstants.getOrCreate(ST, V); 0
1333 } ----
1334 ----
1335 ConstantVector::ConstantVector(VectorType *T, ArrayRef V) 0
1336 : ConstantAggregate(T, ConstantVectorVal, V) { 0
1337 assert(V.size() == cast(T)->getNumElements() && 0
1338 "Invalid initializer for constant vector"); ----
1339 } 0
1340 ----
1341 // ConstantVector accessors. ----
1342 Constant *ConstantVector::get(ArrayRef V) { 0
1343 if (Constant *C = getImpl(V)) 0
1344 return C; 0
1345 auto *Ty = FixedVectorType::get(V.front()->getType(), V.size()); 0
1346 return Ty->getContext().pImpl->VectorConstants.getOrCreate(Ty, V); 0
1347 } ----
1348 ----
1349 Constant *ConstantVector::getImpl(ArrayRef V) { 0
1350 assert(!V.empty() && "Vectors can't be empty"); 0
1351 auto *T = FixedVectorType::get(V.front()->getType(), V.size()); 0
1352 ----
1353 // If this is an all-undef or all-zero vector, return a ----
1354 // ConstantAggregateZero or UndefValue. ----
1355 Constant *C = V[0]; 0
1356 bool isZero = C->isNullValue(); 0
1357 bool isUndef = isa(C); 0
1358 bool isPoison = isa(C); 0
1359 ----
1360 if (isZero || isUndef) { 0
1361 for (unsigned i = 1, e = V.size(); i != e; ++i) 0
1362 if (V[i] != C) { 0
1363 isZero = isUndef = isPoison = false; 0
1364 break; 0
1365 } ----
1366 } ----
1367 ----
1368 if (isZero) 0
1369 return ConstantAggregateZero::get(T); 0
1370 if (isPoison) 0
1371 return PoisonValue::get(T); 0
1372 if (isUndef) 0
1373 return UndefValue::get(T); 0
1374 ----
1375 // Check to see if all of the elements are ConstantFP or ConstantInt and if ----
1376 // the element type is compatible with ConstantDataVector. If so, use it. ----
1377 if (ConstantDataSequential::isElementTypeCompatible(C->getType())) 0
1378 return getSequenceIfElementsMatch(C, V); 0
1379 ----
1380 // Otherwise, the element type isn't compatible with ConstantDataVector, or ----
1381 // the operand list contains a ConstantExpr or something else strange. ----
1382 return nullptr; 0
1383 } ----
1384 ----
1385 Constant *ConstantVector::getSplat(ElementCount EC, Constant *V) { 0
1386 if (!EC.isScalable()) { 0
1387 // If this splat is compatible with ConstantDataVector, use it instead of ----
1388 // ConstantVector. ----
1389 if ((isa(V) || isa(V)) && 0
1390 ConstantDataSequential::isElementTypeCompatible(V->getType())) 0
1391 return ConstantDataVector::getSplat(EC.getKnownMinValue(), V); 0
1392 ----
1393 SmallVector Elts(EC.getKnownMinValue(), V); 0
1394 return get(Elts); 0
1395 } 0
1396 ----
1397 Type *VTy = VectorType::get(V->getType(), EC); 0
1398 ----
1399 if (V->isNullValue()) 0
1400 return ConstantAggregateZero::get(VTy); 0
1401 else if (isa(V)) 0
1402 return UndefValue::get(VTy); 0
1403 ----
1404 Type *IdxTy = Type::getInt64Ty(VTy->getContext()); 0
1405 ----
1406 // Move scalar into vector. ----
1407 Constant *PoisonV = PoisonValue::get(VTy); 0
1408 V = ConstantExpr::getInsertElement(PoisonV, V, ConstantInt::get(IdxTy, 0)); 0
1409 // Build shuffle mask to perform the splat. ----
1410 SmallVector Zeros(EC.getKnownMinValue(), 0); 0
1411 // Splat. ----
1412 return ConstantExpr::getShuffleVector(V, PoisonV, Zeros); 0
1413 } 0

1416 LLVMContextImpl *pImpl = Context.pImpl; 0
1417 if (!pImpl->TheNoneToken) 0
1418 pImpl->TheNoneToken.reset(new ConstantTokenNone(Context)); 0
1419 return pImpl->TheNoneToken.get(); 0
1420 } ----

1449 ----
1450 Constant *ConstantExpr::getWithOperands(ArrayRef Ops, Type *Ty, 0
1451 bool OnlyIfReduced, Type *SrcTy) const { ----
1452 assert(Ops.size() == getNumOperands() && "Operand count mismatch!"); 0
1453 ----
1454 // If no operands changed return self. ----
1455 if (Ty == getType() && std::equal(Ops.begin(), Ops.end(), op_begin())) 0
1456 return const_cast(this); 0
1457 ----
1458 Type *OnlyIfReducedTy = OnlyIfReduced ? Ty : nullptr; 0
1459 switch (getOpcode()) { 0
1460 case Instruction::Trunc: 0
1461 case Instruction::ZExt: ----
1462 case Instruction::SExt: ----
1463 case Instruction::FPTrunc: ----
1464 case Instruction::FPExt: ----
1465 case Instruction::UIToFP: ----
1466 case Instruction::SIToFP: ----
1467 case Instruction::FPToUI: ----
1468 case Instruction::FPToSI: ----
1469 case Instruction::PtrToInt: ----
1470 case Instruction::IntToPtr: ----
1471 case Instruction::BitCast: ----
1472 case Instruction::AddrSpaceCast: ----
1473 return ConstantExpr::getCast(getOpcode(), Ops[0], Ty, OnlyIfReduced); 0
1474 case Instruction::InsertElement: 0
1475 return ConstantExpr::getInsertElement(Ops[0], Ops[1], Ops[2], 0
1476 OnlyIfReducedTy); 0
1477 case Instruction::ExtractElement: 0
1478 return ConstantExpr::getExtractElement(Ops[0], Ops[1], OnlyIfReducedTy); 0
1479 case Instruction::ShuffleVector: 0
1480 return ConstantExpr::getShuffleVector(Ops[0], Ops[1], getShuffleMask(), 0
1481 OnlyIfReducedTy); 0
1482 case Instruction::GetElementPtr: { 0
1483 auto *GEPO = cast(this); 0
1484 assert(SrcTy || (Ops[0]->getType() == getOperand(0)->getType())); 0
1485 return ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr( 0
1486 SrcTy ? SrcTy : GEPO->getSourceElementType(), Ops[0], Ops.slice(1), 0
1487 GEPO->isInBounds(), GEPO->getInRangeIndex(), OnlyIfReducedTy); 0
1488 } ----
1489 case Instruction::ICmp: 0
1490 case Instruction::FCmp: ----
1491 return ConstantExpr::getCompare(getPredicate(), Ops[0], Ops[1], 0
1492 OnlyIfReducedTy); 0
1493 default: 0
1494 assert(getNumOperands() == 2 && "Must be binary operator?"); 0
1495 return ConstantExpr::get(getOpcode(), Ops[0], Ops[1], SubclassOptionalData, 0
1496 OnlyIfReducedTy); 0
1497 } ----
1498 } ----

1512 unsigned NumBits = Ty->getIntegerBitWidth(); 0
1513 if (Ty->isIntegerTy(1)) 0
1514 return Val == 0 || Val == 1 || Val == -1; 0
1515 return isIntN(NumBits, Val); 0
1516 } ----
1517 ----
1518 bool ConstantFP::isValueValidForType(Type *Ty, const APFloat& Val) { 0
1519 // convert modifies in place, so make a copy. ----
1520 APFloat Val2 = APFloat(Val); 0
1521 bool losesInfo; ----
1522 switch (Ty->getTypeID()) { 0
1523 default: 0
1524 return false; // These can't be represented as floating point! 0
1525 ----
1526 // FIXME rounding mode needs to be more flexible ----
1527 case Type::HalfTyID: { 0
1528 if (&Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEhalf()) 0
1529 return true; 0
1530 Val2.convert(APFloat::IEEEhalf(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &losesInfo); 0
1531 return !losesInfo; 0
1532 } ----
1533 case Type::BFloatTyID: { 0
1534 if (&Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::BFloat()) 0
1535 return true; 0
1536 Val2.convert(APFloat::BFloat(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &losesInfo); 0
1537 return !losesInfo; 0
1538 } ----
1539 case Type::FloatTyID: { 0
1540 if (&Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEsingle()) 0
1541 return true; 0
1542 Val2.convert(APFloat::IEEEsingle(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &losesInfo); 0
1543 return !losesInfo; 0
1544 } ----
1545 case Type::DoubleTyID: { 0
1546 if (&Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEhalf() || 0
1547 &Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::BFloat() || 0
1548 &Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEsingle() || 0
1549 &Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEdouble()) 0
1550 return true; 0
1551 Val2.convert(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &losesInfo); 0
1552 return !losesInfo; 0
1553 } ----
1554 case Type::X86_FP80TyID: 0
1555 return &Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEhalf() || 0
1556 &Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::BFloat() || 0
1557 &Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEsingle() || 0
1558 &Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEdouble() || 0
1559 &Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::x87DoubleExtended(); 0
1560 case Type::FP128TyID: 0
1561 return &Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEhalf() || 0
1562 &Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::BFloat() || 0
1563 &Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEsingle() || 0
1564 &Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEdouble() || 0
1565 &Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEquad(); 0
1566 case Type::PPC_FP128TyID: 0
1567 return &Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEhalf() || 0
1568 &Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::BFloat() || 0
1569 &Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEsingle() || 0
1570 &Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEdouble() || 0
1571 &Val2.getSemantics() == &APFloat::PPCDoubleDouble(); 0
1572 } ----
1573 } 0

1579 ConstantAggregateZero *ConstantAggregateZero::get(Type *Ty) { 0
1580 assert((Ty->isStructTy() || Ty->isArrayTy() || Ty->isVectorTy()) && 0
1581 "Cannot create an aggregate zero of non-aggregate type!"); ----
1582 ----
1583 std::unique_ptr &Entry = ----
1584 Ty->getContext().pImpl->CAZConstants[Ty]; 0

1589 } ----

1614 ----
1615 Constant *Constant::getSplatValue(bool AllowUndefs) const { 0
1616 assert(this->getType()->isVectorTy() && "Only valid for vectors!"); 0
1617 if (isa(this)) 0
1618 return getNullValue(cast(getType())->getElementType()); 0
1619 if (const ConstantDataVector *CV = dyn_cast(this)) 0
1620 return CV->getSplatValue(); 0
1621 if (const ConstantVector *CV = dyn_cast(this)) 0
1622 return CV->getSplatValue(AllowUndefs); 0
1623 ----
1624 // Check if this is a constant expression splat of the form returned by ----
1625 // ConstantVector::getSplat() ----
1626 const auto *Shuf = dyn_cast(this); 0
1627 if (Shuf && Shuf->getOpcode() == Instruction::ShuffleVector && 0
1628 isa(Shuf->getOperand(1))) { 0
1629 ----
1630 const auto *IElt = dyn_cast(Shuf->getOperand(0)); 0
1631 if (IElt && IElt->getOpcode() == Instruction::InsertElement && 0
1632 isa(IElt->getOperand(0))) { 0
1633 ----
1634 ArrayRef Mask = Shuf->getShuffleMask(); 0
1635 Constant *SplatVal = IElt->getOperand(1); 0
1636 ConstantInt *Index = dyn_cast(IElt->getOperand(2)); 0
1637 ----
1638 if (Index && Index->getValue() == 0 && 0
1639 llvm::all_of(Mask, [](int I) { return I == 0; })) 0
1640 return SplatVal; 0
1641 } ----
1642 } ----
1643 ----
1644 return nullptr; 0
1645 } ----
1646 ----
1647 Constant *ConstantVector::getSplatValue(bool AllowUndefs) const { 0
1648 // Check out first element. ----
1649 Constant *Elt = getOperand(0); 0
1650 // Then make sure all remaining elements point to the same value. ----
1651 for (unsigned I = 1, E = getNumOperands(); I < E; ++I) { 0
1652 Constant *OpC = getOperand(I); 0
1653 if (OpC == Elt) 0
1654 continue; 0
1655 ----
1656 // Strict mode: any mismatch is not a splat. ----
1657 if (!AllowUndefs) 0
1658 return nullptr; 0
1659 ----
1660 // Allow undefs mode: ignore undefined elements. ----
1661 if (isa(OpC)) 0
1662 continue; 0
1663 ----
1664 // If we do not have a defined element yet, use the current operand. ----
1665 if (isa(Elt)) 0
1666 Elt = OpC; 0
1667 ----
1668 if (OpC != Elt) 0
1669 return nullptr; 0
1670 } ----
1671 return Elt; 0
1672 } ----
1673 ----
1674 const APInt &Constant::getUniqueInteger() const { 0
1675 if (const ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast(this)) 0
1676 return CI->getValue(); 0
1677 // Scalable vectors can use a ConstantExpr to build a splat. ----
1678 if (isa(this)) 0
1679 return cast(this->getSplatValue())->getValue(); 0
1680 // For non-ConstantExpr we use getAggregateElement as a fast path to avoid ----
1681 // calling getSplatValue in release builds. ----
1682 assert(this->getSplatValue() && "Doesn't contain a unique integer!"); 0
1683 const Constant *C = this->getAggregateElement(0U); 0
1684 assert(C && isa(C) && "Not a vector of numbers!"); 0
1685 return cast(C)->getValue(); 0
1686 } ----

1761 ----
1762 BlockAddress *BlockAddress::get(Function *F, BasicBlock *BB) { 0
1763 BlockAddress *&BA = ----
1764 F->getContext().pImpl->BlockAddresses[std::make_pair(F, BB)]; 0
1765 if (!BA) 0
1766 BA = new BlockAddress(F, BB); 0
1767 ----
1768 assert(BA->getFunction() == F && "Basic block moved between functions"); 0
1769 return BA; 0
1770 } ----
1771 ----
1772 BlockAddress::BlockAddress(Function *F, BasicBlock *BB) 0
1773 : Constant(Type::getInt8PtrTy(F->getContext(), F->getAddressSpace()), 0
1774 Value::BlockAddressVal, &Op<0>(), 2) { 0
1775 setOperand(0, F); 0
1776 setOperand(1, BB); 0
1777 BB->AdjustBlockAddressRefCount(1); 0
1778 } 0
1779 ----
1780 BlockAddress *BlockAddress::lookup(const BasicBlock *BB) { 0
1781 if (!BB->hasAddressTaken()) 0
1782 return nullptr; 0
1783 ----
1784 const Function *F = BB->getParent(); 0
1785 assert(F && "Block must have a parent"); 0
1786 BlockAddress *BA = ----
1787 F->getContext().pImpl->BlockAddresses.lookup(std::make_pair(F, BB)); 0
1788 assert(BA && "Refcount and block address map disagree!"); 0
1789 return BA; 0
1790 } ----
1791 ----
1792 /// Remove the constant from the constant table. ----
1793 void BlockAddress::destroyConstantImpl() { 0
1794 getFunction()->getType()->getContext().pImpl 0
1795 ->BlockAddresses.erase(std::make_pair(getFunction(), getBasicBlock())); 0
1796 getBasicBlock()->AdjustBlockAddressRefCount(-1); 0
1797 } 0
1798 ----
1799 Value *BlockAddress::handleOperandChangeImpl(Value *From, Value *To) { 0
1800 // This could be replacing either the Basic Block or the Function. In either ----
1801 // case, we have to remove the map entry. ----
1802 Function *NewF = getFunction(); 0
1803 BasicBlock *NewBB = getBasicBlock(); 0
1804 ----
1805 if (From == NewF) 0
1806 NewF = cast(To->stripPointerCasts()); 0
1807 else { ----
1808 assert(From == NewBB && "From does not match any operand"); 0
1809 NewBB = cast(To); 0
1810 } ----
1811 ----
1812 // See if the 'new' entry already exists, if not, just update this in place ----
1813 // and return early. ----
1814 BlockAddress *&NewBA = ----
1815 getContext().pImpl->BlockAddresses[std::make_pair(NewF, NewBB)]; 0
1816 if (NewBA) 0
1817 return NewBA; 0
1818 ----
1819 getBasicBlock()->AdjustBlockAddressRefCount(-1); 0
1820 ----
1821 // Remove the old entry, this can't cause the map to rehash (just a ----
1822 // tombstone will get added). ----
1823 getContext().pImpl->BlockAddresses.erase(std::make_pair(getFunction(), 0
1824 getBasicBlock())); 0
1825 NewBA = this; 0
1826 setOperand(0, NewF); 0
1827 setOperand(1, NewBB); 0
1828 getBasicBlock()->AdjustBlockAddressRefCount(1); 0
1829 ----
1830 // If we just want to keep the existing value, then return null. ----
1831 // Callers know that this means we shouldn't delete this value. ----
1832 return nullptr; 0
1833 } ----
1834 ----
1835 DSOLocalEquivalent *DSOLocalEquivalent::get(GlobalValue *GV) { 0
1836 DSOLocalEquivalent *&Equiv = GV->getContext().pImpl->DSOLocalEquivalents[GV]; 0
1837 if (!Equiv) 0
1838 Equiv = new DSOLocalEquivalent(GV); 0
1839 ----
1840 assert(Equiv->getGlobalValue() == GV && 0
1841 "DSOLocalFunction does not match the expected global value"); ----
1842 return Equiv; 0
1843 } ----
1844 ----
1845 DSOLocalEquivalent::DSOLocalEquivalent(GlobalValue *GV) 0
1846 : Constant(GV->getType(), Value::DSOLocalEquivalentVal, &Op<0>(), 1) { 0
1847 setOperand(0, GV); 0
1848 } 0
1849 ----
1850 /// Remove the constant from the constant table. ----
1851 void DSOLocalEquivalent::destroyConstantImpl() { 0
1852 const GlobalValue *GV = getGlobalValue(); 0
1853 GV->getContext().pImpl->DSOLocalEquivalents.erase(GV); 0
1854 } 0
1855 ----
1856 Value *DSOLocalEquivalent::handleOperandChangeImpl(Value *From, Value *To) { 0
1857 assert(From == getGlobalValue() && "Changing value does not match operand."); 0
1858 assert(isa(To) && "Can only replace the operands with a constant"); 0
1859 ----
1860 // The replacement is with another global value. ----
1861 if (const auto *ToObj = dyn_cast(To)) { 0
1862 DSOLocalEquivalent *&NewEquiv = ----
1863 getContext().pImpl->DSOLocalEquivalents[ToObj]; 0
1864 if (NewEquiv) 0
1865 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(NewEquiv, getType()); 0
1866 } ----
1867 ----
1868 // If the argument is replaced with a null value, just replace this constant ----
1869 // with a null value. ----
1870 if (cast(To)->isNullValue()) 0
1871 return To; 0
1872 ----
1873 // The replacement could be a bitcast or an alias to another function. We can ----
1874 // replace it with a bitcast to the dso_local_equivalent of that function. ----
1875 auto *Func = cast(To->stripPointerCastsAndAliases()); 0
1876 DSOLocalEquivalent *&NewEquiv = getContext().pImpl->DSOLocalEquivalents[Func]; 0
1877 if (NewEquiv) 0
1878 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(NewEquiv, getType()); 0
1879 ----
1880 // Replace this with the new one. ----
1881 getContext().pImpl->DSOLocalEquivalents.erase(getGlobalValue()); 0
1882 NewEquiv = this; 0
1883 setOperand(0, Func); 0
1884 ----
1885 if (Func->getType() != getType()) { 0
1886 // It is ok to mutate the type here because this constant should always ----
1887 // reflect the type of the function it's holding. ----
1888 mutateType(Func->getType()); 0
1889 } ----
1890 return nullptr; 0
1891 } ----
1892 ----
1893 NoCFIValue *NoCFIValue::get(GlobalValue *GV) { 0
1894 NoCFIValue *&NC = GV->getContext().pImpl->NoCFIValues[GV]; 0
1895 if (!NC) 0
1896 NC = new NoCFIValue(GV); 0
1897 ----
1898 assert(NC->getGlobalValue() == GV && 0
1899 "NoCFIValue does not match the expected global value"); ----
1900 return NC; 0
1901 } ----
1902 ----
1903 NoCFIValue::NoCFIValue(GlobalValue *GV) 0
1904 : Constant(GV->getType(), Value::NoCFIValueVal, &Op<0>(), 1) { 0
1905 setOperand(0, GV); 0
1906 } 0
1907 ----
1908 /// Remove the constant from the constant table. ----

1911 GV->getContext().pImpl->NoCFIValues.erase(GV); 0
1912 } 0
1913 ----
1914 Value *NoCFIValue::handleOperandChangeImpl(Value *From, Value *To) { 0
1915 assert(From == getGlobalValue() && "Changing value does not match operand."); 0
1916 ----
1917 GlobalValue *GV = dyn_cast(To->stripPointerCasts()); 0
1918 assert(GV && "Can only replace the operands with a global value"); 0
1919 ----
1920 NoCFIValue *&NewNC = getContext().pImpl->NoCFIValues[GV]; 0
1921 if (NewNC) 0
1922 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(NewNC, getType()); 0
1923 ----
1924 getContext().pImpl->NoCFIValues.erase(getGlobalValue()); 0
1925 NewNC = this; 0
1926 setOperand(0, GV); 0
1927 ----
1928 if (GV->getType() != getType()) 0
1929 mutateType(GV->getType()); 0
1930 ----
1931 return nullptr; 0
1932 } ----

1936 ----
1937 /// This is a utility function to handle folding of casts and lookup of the ----
1938 /// cast in the ExprConstants map. It is used by the various get* methods below. ----
1939 static Constant *getFoldedCast(Instruction::CastOps opc, Constant *C, Type *Ty, 0
1940 bool OnlyIfReduced = false) { ----
1941 assert(Ty->isFirstClassType() && "Cannot cast to an aggregate type!"); 0
1942 // Fold a few common cases ----
1943 if (Constant *FC = ConstantFoldCastInstruction(opc, C, Ty)) 0
1944 return FC; 0
1945 ----
1946 if (OnlyIfReduced) 0
1947 return nullptr; 0
1948 ----
1949 LLVMContextImpl *pImpl = Ty->getContext().pImpl; 0
1950 ----
1951 // Look up the constant in the table first to ensure uniqueness. ----
1952 ConstantExprKeyType Key(opc, C); 0
1953 ----
1954 return pImpl->ExprConstants.getOrCreate(Ty, Key); 0
1955 } ----
1956 ----
1957 Constant *ConstantExpr::getCast(unsigned oc, Constant *C, Type *Ty, 0
1958 bool OnlyIfReduced) { ----
1959 Instruction::CastOps opc = Instruction::CastOps(oc); 0
1960 assert(Instruction::isCast(opc) && "opcode out of range"); 0
1961 assert(C && Ty && "Null arguments to getCast"); 0
1962 assert(CastInst::castIsValid(opc, C, Ty) && "Invalid constantexpr cast!"); 0
1963 ----
1964 switch (opc) { 0
1965 default: 0
1966 llvm_unreachable("Invalid cast opcode"); 0
1967 case Instruction::Trunc: 0
1968 return getTrunc(C, Ty, OnlyIfReduced); 0
1969 case Instruction::ZExt: 0
1970 return getZExt(C, Ty, OnlyIfReduced); 0
1971 case Instruction::SExt: 0
1972 return getSExt(C, Ty, OnlyIfReduced); 0
1973 case Instruction::FPTrunc: 0
1974 return getFPTrunc(C, Ty, OnlyIfReduced); 0
1975 case Instruction::FPExt: 0
1976 return getFPExtend(C, Ty, OnlyIfReduced); 0
1977 case Instruction::UIToFP: 0
1978 return getUIToFP(C, Ty, OnlyIfReduced); 0
1979 case Instruction::SIToFP: 0
1980 return getSIToFP(C, Ty, OnlyIfReduced); 0
1981 case Instruction::FPToUI: 0
1982 return getFPToUI(C, Ty, OnlyIfReduced); 0
1983 case Instruction::FPToSI: 0
1984 return getFPToSI(C, Ty, OnlyIfReduced); 0
1985 case Instruction::PtrToInt: 0
1986 return getPtrToInt(C, Ty, OnlyIfReduced); 0
1987 case Instruction::IntToPtr: 0
1988 return getIntToPtr(C, Ty, OnlyIfReduced); 0
1989 case Instruction::BitCast: 0
1990 return getBitCast(C, Ty, OnlyIfReduced); 0
1991 case Instruction::AddrSpaceCast: 0
1992 return getAddrSpaceCast(C, Ty, OnlyIfReduced); 0
1993 } ----
1994 } ----
1995 ----
1996 Constant *ConstantExpr::getZExtOrBitCast(Constant *C, Type *Ty) { 0
1997 if (C->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits() == Ty->getScalarSizeInBits()) 0
1998 return getBitCast(C, Ty); 0
1999 return getZExt(C, Ty); 0
2000 } ----

2005 return getSExt(C, Ty); 0

2008 Constant *ConstantExpr::getTruncOrBitCast(Constant *C, Type *Ty) { 0

2010 return getBitCast(C, Ty); 0
2011 return getTrunc(C, Ty); 0

2013 ----
2014 Constant *ConstantExpr::getSExtOrTrunc(Constant *C, Type *Ty) { 0
2015 assert(C->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy() && Ty->isIntOrIntVectorTy() && 0
2016 "Can only sign extend/truncate integers!"); ----
2017 Type *CTy = C->getType(); 0
2018 if (CTy->getScalarSizeInBits() < Ty->getScalarSizeInBits()) 0
2019 return getSExt(C, Ty); 0
2020 if (CTy->getScalarSizeInBits() > Ty->getScalarSizeInBits()) 0
2021 return getTrunc(C, Ty); 0
2022 return C; 0
2023 } ----
2024 ----
2025 Constant *ConstantExpr::getPointerCast(Constant *S, Type *Ty) { 0
2026 assert(S->getType()->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() && "Invalid cast"); 0
2027 assert((Ty->isIntOrIntVectorTy() || Ty->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy()) && 0
2028 "Invalid cast"); ----
2029 ----
2030 if (Ty->isIntOrIntVectorTy()) 0
2031 return getPtrToInt(S, Ty); 0
2032 ----
2033 unsigned SrcAS = S->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace(); 0
2034 if (Ty->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() && SrcAS != Ty->getPointerAddressSpace()) 0
2035 return getAddrSpaceCast(S, Ty); 0
2036 ----
2037 return getBitCast(S, Ty); 0
2038 } ----
2039 ----
2040 Constant *ConstantExpr::getPointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(Constant *S, 0
2041 Type *Ty) { ----
2042 assert(S->getType()->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() && "Invalid cast"); 0
2043 assert(Ty->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() && "Invalid cast"); 0
2044 ----
2045 if (S->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() != Ty->getPointerAddressSpace()) 0
2046 return getAddrSpaceCast(S, Ty); 0
2047 ----
2048 return getBitCast(S, Ty); 0
2049 } ----
2050 ----
2051 Constant *ConstantExpr::getIntegerCast(Constant *C, Type *Ty, bool isSigned) { 0
2052 assert(C->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy() && 0
2053 Ty->isIntOrIntVectorTy() && "Invalid cast"); ----
2054 unsigned SrcBits = C->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
2055 unsigned DstBits = Ty->getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
2056 Instruction::CastOps opcode = 0
2057 (SrcBits == DstBits ? Instruction::BitCast : 0
2058 (SrcBits > DstBits ? Instruction::Trunc : 0
2059 (isSigned ? Instruction::SExt : Instruction::ZExt))); 0
2060 return getCast(opcode, C, Ty); 0
2061 } ----
2062 ----
2063 Constant *ConstantExpr::getFPCast(Constant *C, Type *Ty) { 0
2064 assert(C->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy() && Ty->isFPOrFPVectorTy() && 0
2065 "Invalid cast"); ----
2066 unsigned SrcBits = C->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
2067 unsigned DstBits = Ty->getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
2068 if (SrcBits == DstBits) 0
2069 return C; // Avoid a useless cast 0
2070 Instruction::CastOps opcode = 0
2071 (SrcBits > DstBits ? Instruction::FPTrunc : Instruction::FPExt); 0
2072 return getCast(opcode, C, Ty); 0
2073 } ----

2075 Constant *ConstantExpr::getTrunc(Constant *C, Type *Ty, bool OnlyIfReduced) { 0
2076 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
2077 bool fromVec = isa(C->getType()); 0
2078 bool toVec = isa(Ty); 0
2079 #endif ----
2080 assert((fromVec == toVec) && "Cannot convert from scalar to/from vector"); 0
2081 assert(C->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy() && "Trunc operand must be integer"); 0
2082 assert(Ty->isIntOrIntVectorTy() && "Trunc produces only integral"); 0
2083 assert(C->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits() > Ty->getScalarSizeInBits()&& 0
2084 "SrcTy must be larger than DestTy for Trunc!"); ----
2085 ----
2086 return getFoldedCast(Instruction::Trunc, C, Ty, OnlyIfReduced); 0
2087 } ----

2231 ----
2232 Constant *ConstantExpr::get(unsigned Opcode, Constant *C1, Constant *C2, 0
2233 unsigned Flags, Type *OnlyIfReducedTy) { ----
2234 // Check the operands for consistency first. ----
2235 assert(Instruction::isBinaryOp(Opcode) && 0
2236 "Invalid opcode in binary constant expression"); ----
2237 assert(isSupportedBinOp(Opcode) && 0
2238 "Binop not supported as constant expression"); ----
2239 assert(C1->getType() == C2->getType() && 0
2240 "Operand types in binary constant expression should match"); ----
2241 ----
2242 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
2243 switch (Opcode) { 0
2244 case Instruction::Add: 0
2245 case Instruction::Sub: ----
2246 case Instruction::Mul: ----
2247 assert(C1->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy() && 0
2248 "Tried to create an integer operation on a non-integer type!"); ----
2249 break; 0
2250 case Instruction::And: 0
2251 case Instruction::Or: ----
2252 case Instruction::Xor: ----
2253 assert(C1->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy() && 0
2254 "Tried to create a logical operation on a non-integral type!"); ----
2255 break; 0
2256 case Instruction::Shl: 0
2257 case Instruction::LShr: ----
2258 case Instruction::AShr: ----
2259 assert(C1->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy() && 0
2260 "Tried to create a shift operation on a non-integer type!"); ----
2261 break; 0
2262 default: 0
2263 break; 0
2264 } ----
2265 #endif ----
2266 ----
2267 if (Constant *FC = ConstantFoldBinaryInstruction(Opcode, C1, C2)) 0
2268 return FC; 0
2269 ----
2270 if (OnlyIfReducedTy == C1->getType()) 0
2271 return nullptr; 0
2272 ----
2273 Constant *ArgVec[] = { C1, C2 }; 0
2274 ConstantExprKeyType Key(Opcode, ArgVec, 0, Flags); 0
2275 ----
2276 LLVMContextImpl *pImpl = C1->getContext().pImpl; 0
2277 return pImpl->ExprConstants.getOrCreate(C1->getType(), Key); 0
2278 } ----
2279 ----
2280 bool ConstantExpr::isDesirableBinOp(unsigned Opcode) { 0
2281 switch (Opcode) { 0
2282 case Instruction::UDiv: 0
2283 case Instruction::SDiv: ----
2284 case Instruction::URem: ----
2285 case Instruction::SRem: ----
2286 case Instruction::FAdd: ----
2287 case Instruction::FSub: ----
2288 case Instruction::FMul: ----
2289 case Instruction::FDiv: ----
2290 case Instruction::FRem: ----
2291 return false; 0
2292 case Instruction::Add: 0
2293 case Instruction::Sub: ----
2294 case Instruction::Mul: ----
2295 case Instruction::Shl: ----
2296 case Instruction::LShr: ----
2297 case Instruction::AShr: ----
2298 case Instruction::And: ----
2299 case Instruction::Or: ----
2300 case Instruction::Xor: ----
2301 return true; 0
2302 default: 0
2303 llvm_unreachable("Argument must be binop opcode"); 0
2304 } ----
2305 } ----
2306 ----
2307 bool ConstantExpr::isSupportedBinOp(unsigned Opcode) { 0
2308 switch (Opcode) { 0
2309 case Instruction::UDiv: 0
2310 case Instruction::SDiv: ----
2311 case Instruction::URem: ----
2312 case Instruction::SRem: ----
2313 case Instruction::FAdd: ----
2314 case Instruction::FSub: ----
2315 case Instruction::FMul: ----
2316 case Instruction::FDiv: ----
2317 case Instruction::FRem: ----
2318 return false; 0
2319 case Instruction::Add: 0
2320 case Instruction::Sub: ----
2321 case Instruction::Mul: ----
2322 case Instruction::Shl: ----
2323 case Instruction::LShr: ----
2324 case Instruction::AShr: ----
2325 case Instruction::And: ----
2326 case Instruction::Or: ----
2327 case Instruction::Xor: ----
2328 return true; 0
2329 default: 0
2330 llvm_unreachable("Argument must be binop opcode"); 0
2331 } ----
2332 } ----
2333 ----
2334 Constant *ConstantExpr::getSizeOf(Type* Ty) { 0
2335 // sizeof is implemented as: (i64) gep (Ty*)null, 1 ----
2336 // Note that a non-inbounds gep is used, as null isn't within any object. ----
2337 Constant *GEPIdx = ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt32Ty(Ty->getContext()), 1); 0
2338 Constant *GEP = getGetElementPtr( 0
2339 Ty, Constant::getNullValue(PointerType::getUnqual(Ty)), GEPIdx); 0
2340 return getPtrToInt(GEP, 0
2341 Type::getInt64Ty(Ty->getContext())); 0
2342 } ----
2343 ----
2344 Constant *ConstantExpr::getAlignOf(Type* Ty) { 0
2345 // alignof is implemented as: (i64) gep ({i1,Ty}*)null, 0, 1 ----
2346 // Note that a non-inbounds gep is used, as null isn't within any object. ----
2347 Type *AligningTy = StructType::get(Type::getInt1Ty(Ty->getContext()), Ty); 0
2348 Constant *NullPtr = Constant::getNullValue(AligningTy->getPointerTo(0)); 0
2349 Constant *Zero = ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt64Ty(Ty->getContext()), 0); 0
2350 Constant *One = ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt32Ty(Ty->getContext()), 1); 0
2351 Constant *Indices[2] = { Zero, One }; 0
2352 Constant *GEP = getGetElementPtr(AligningTy, NullPtr, Indices); 0
2353 return getPtrToInt(GEP, 0
2354 Type::getInt64Ty(Ty->getContext())); 0
2355 } ----
2356 ----
2357 Constant *ConstantExpr::getCompare(unsigned short Predicate, Constant *C1, 0
2358 Constant *C2, bool OnlyIfReduced) { ----
2359 assert(C1->getType() == C2->getType() && "Op types should be identical!"); 0
2360 ----
2361 switch (Predicate) { 0
2362 default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid CmpInst predicate"); 0
2363 case CmpInst::FCMP_FALSE: case CmpInst::FCMP_OEQ: case CmpInst::FCMP_OGT: 0
2364 case CmpInst::FCMP_OGE: case CmpInst::FCMP_OLT: case CmpInst::FCMP_OLE: ----
2365 case CmpInst::FCMP_ONE: case CmpInst::FCMP_ORD: case CmpInst::FCMP_UNO: ----
2366 case CmpInst::FCMP_UEQ: case CmpInst::FCMP_UGT: case CmpInst::FCMP_UGE: ----
2367 case CmpInst::FCMP_ULT: case CmpInst::FCMP_ULE: case CmpInst::FCMP_UNE: ----
2368 case CmpInst::FCMP_TRUE: ----
2369 return getFCmp(Predicate, C1, C2, OnlyIfReduced); 0
2370 ----
2371 case CmpInst::ICMP_EQ: case CmpInst::ICMP_NE: case CmpInst::ICMP_UGT: 0
2372 case CmpInst::ICMP_UGE: case CmpInst::ICMP_ULT: case CmpInst::ICMP_ULE: ----
2373 case CmpInst::ICMP_SGT: case CmpInst::ICMP_SGE: case CmpInst::ICMP_SLT: ----
2374 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLE: ----
2375 return getICmp(Predicate, C1, C2, OnlyIfReduced); 0
2376 } ----
2377 } ----
2378 ----
2379 Constant *ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(Type *Ty, Constant *C, 0
2380 ArrayRef Idxs, bool InBounds, ----
2381 std::optional InRangeIndex, ----
2382 Type *OnlyIfReducedTy) { ----
2383 assert(Ty && "Must specify element type"); 0
2384 assert(isSupportedGetElementPtr(Ty) && "Element type is unsupported!"); 0
2385 ----
2386 if (Constant *FC = 0
2387 ConstantFoldGetElementPtr(Ty, C, InBounds, InRangeIndex, Idxs)) 0
2388 return FC; // Fold a few common cases. 0
2389 ----
2390 assert(GetElementPtrInst::getIndexedType(Ty, Idxs) && 0
2391 "GEP indices invalid!");; ----
2392 ----
2393 // Get the result type of the getelementptr! ----
2394 Type *ReqTy = GetElementPtrInst::getGEPReturnType(C, Idxs); 0
2395 if (OnlyIfReducedTy == ReqTy) 0
2396 return nullptr; 0
2397 ----
2398 auto EltCount = ElementCount::getFixed(0); 0
2399 if (VectorType *VecTy = dyn_cast(ReqTy)) 0
2400 EltCount = VecTy->getElementCount(); 0
2401 ----
2402 // Look up the constant in the table first to ensure uniqueness ----
2403 std::vector ArgVec; 0
2404 ArgVec.reserve(1 + Idxs.size()); 0
2405 ArgVec.push_back(C); 0
2406 auto GTI = gep_type_begin(Ty, Idxs), GTE = gep_type_end(Ty, Idxs); 0
2407 for (; GTI != GTE; ++GTI) { 0
2408 auto *Idx = cast(GTI.getOperand()); 0
2409 assert( 0
2410 (!isa(Idx->getType()) || ----
2411 cast(Idx->getType())->getElementCount() == EltCount) && ----
2412 "getelementptr index type missmatch"); ----
2413 ----
2414 if (GTI.isStruct() && Idx->getType()->isVectorTy()) { 0
2415 Idx = Idx->getSplatValue(); 0
2416 } else if (GTI.isSequential() && EltCount.isNonZero() && 0
2417 !Idx->getType()->isVectorTy()) { 0
2418 Idx = ConstantVector::getSplat(EltCount, Idx); 0
2419 } ----
2420 ArgVec.push_back(Idx); 0
2421 } ----
2422 ----
2423 unsigned SubClassOptionalData = InBounds ? GEPOperator::IsInBounds : 0; 0
2424 if (InRangeIndex && *InRangeIndex < 63) 0
2425 SubClassOptionalData |= (*InRangeIndex + 1) << 1; 0
2426 const ConstantExprKeyType Key(Instruction::GetElementPtr, ArgVec, 0, ----
2427 SubClassOptionalData, std::nullopt, Ty); 0
2428 ----
2429 LLVMContextImpl *pImpl = C->getContext().pImpl; 0
2430 return pImpl->ExprConstants.getOrCreate(ReqTy, Key); 0
2431 } 0
2432 ----
2433 Constant *ConstantExpr::getICmp(unsigned short pred, Constant *LHS, 0
2434 Constant *RHS, bool OnlyIfReduced) { ----
2435 auto Predicate = static_cast(pred); 0
2436 assert(LHS->getType() == RHS->getType()); 0
2437 assert(CmpInst::isIntPredicate(Predicate) && "Invalid ICmp Predicate"); 0
2438 ----
2439 if (Constant *FC = ConstantFoldCompareInstruction(Predicate, LHS, RHS)) 0
2440 return FC; // Fold a few common cases... 0
2441 ----
2442 if (OnlyIfReduced) 0
2443 return nullptr; 0
2444 ----
2445 // Look up the constant in the table first to ensure uniqueness ----
2446 Constant *ArgVec[] = { LHS, RHS }; 0
2447 // Get the key type with both the opcode and predicate ----
2448 const ConstantExprKeyType Key(Instruction::ICmp, ArgVec, Predicate); 0
2449 ----
2450 Type *ResultTy = Type::getInt1Ty(LHS->getContext()); 0
2451 if (VectorType *VT = dyn_cast(LHS->getType())) 0
2452 ResultTy = VectorType::get(ResultTy, VT->getElementCount()); 0
2453 ----
2454 LLVMContextImpl *pImpl = LHS->getType()->getContext().pImpl; 0
2455 return pImpl->ExprConstants.getOrCreate(ResultTy, Key); 0
2456 } ----
2457 ----
2458 Constant *ConstantExpr::getFCmp(unsigned short pred, Constant *LHS, 0
2459 Constant *RHS, bool OnlyIfReduced) { ----
2460 auto Predicate = static_cast(pred); 0
2461 assert(LHS->getType() == RHS->getType()); 0
2462 assert(CmpInst::isFPPredicate(Predicate) && "Invalid FCmp Predicate"); 0
2463 ----
2464 if (Constant *FC = ConstantFoldCompareInstruction(Predicate, LHS, RHS)) 0
2465 return FC; // Fold a few common cases... 0
2466 ----
2467 if (OnlyIfReduced) 0
2468 return nullptr; 0
2469 ----
2470 // Look up the constant in the table first to ensure uniqueness ----
2471 Constant *ArgVec[] = { LHS, RHS }; 0
2472 // Get the key type with both the opcode and predicate ----
2473 const ConstantExprKeyType Key(Instruction::FCmp, ArgVec, Predicate); 0
2474 ----
2475 Type *ResultTy = Type::getInt1Ty(LHS->getContext()); 0
2476 if (VectorType *VT = dyn_cast(LHS->getType())) 0
2477 ResultTy = VectorType::get(ResultTy, VT->getElementCount()); 0
2478 ----

2481 } ----

2487 assert(Idx->getType()->isIntegerTy() && 0

2616 Constant *ConstantExpr::getExactLogBase2(Constant *C) { 0
2617 Type *Ty = C->getType(); 0
2618 const APInt *IVal; ----
2619 if (match(C, m_APInt(IVal)) && IVal->isPowerOf2()) 0
2620 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, IVal->logBase2()); 0
2621 ----
2622 // FIXME: We can extract pow of 2 of splat constant for scalable vectors. ----
2623 auto *VecTy = dyn_cast(Ty); 0
2624 if (!VecTy) 0
2625 return nullptr; 0
2626 ----
2627 SmallVector Elts; 0
2628 for (unsigned I = 0, E = VecTy->getNumElements(); I != E; ++I) { 0
2629 Constant *Elt = C->getAggregateElement(I); 0
2630 if (!Elt) 0
2631 return nullptr; 0
2632 // Note that log2(iN undef) is *NOT* iN undef, because log2(iN undef) u< N. ----
2633 if (isa(Elt)) { 0
2634 Elts.push_back(Constant::getNullValue(Ty->getScalarType())); 0
2635 continue; 0
2636 } ----
2637 if (!match(Elt, m_APInt(IVal)) || !IVal->isPowerOf2()) 0
2638 return nullptr; 0
2639 Elts.push_back(ConstantInt::get(Ty->getScalarType(), IVal->logBase2())); 0
2640 } ----
2641 ----
2642 return ConstantVector::get(Elts); 0
2643 } 0
2644 ----
2645 Constant *ConstantExpr::getBinOpIdentity(unsigned Opcode, Type *Ty, 0
2646 bool AllowRHSConstant, bool NSZ) { ----
2647 assert(Instruction::isBinaryOp(Opcode) && "Only binops allowed"); 0
2648 ----
2649 // Commutative opcodes: it does not matter if AllowRHSConstant is set. ----
2650 if (Instruction::isCommutative(Opcode)) { 0
2651 switch (Opcode) { 0
2652 case Instruction::Add: // X + 0 = X 0
2653 case Instruction::Or: // X | 0 = X ----
2654 case Instruction::Xor: // X ^ 0 = X ----
2655 return Constant::getNullValue(Ty); 0
2656 case Instruction::Mul: // X * 1 = X 0
2657 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, 1); 0
2658 case Instruction::And: // X & -1 = X 0
2659 return Constant::getAllOnesValue(Ty); 0
2660 case Instruction::FAdd: // X + -0.0 = X 0
2661 return ConstantFP::getZero(Ty, !NSZ); 0
2662 case Instruction::FMul: // X * 1.0 = X 0
2663 return ConstantFP::get(Ty, 1.0); 0
2664 default: 0
2665 llvm_unreachable("Every commutative binop has an identity constant"); 0
2666 } ----
2667 } ----
2668 ----
2669 // Non-commutative opcodes: AllowRHSConstant must be set. ----
2670 if (!AllowRHSConstant) 0
2671 return nullptr; 0
2672 ----
2673 switch (Opcode) { 0
2674 case Instruction::Sub: // X - 0 = X 0
2675 case Instruction::Shl: // X << 0 = X ----
2676 case Instruction::LShr: // X >>u 0 = X ----
2677 case Instruction::AShr: // X >> 0 = X ----
2678 case Instruction::FSub: // X - 0.0 = X ----
2679 return Constant::getNullValue(Ty); 0
2680 case Instruction::SDiv: // X / 1 = X 0
2681 case Instruction::UDiv: // X /u 1 = X ----
2682 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, 1); 0
2683 case Instruction::FDiv: // X / 1.0 = X 0
2684 return ConstantFP::get(Ty, 1.0); 0
2685 default: 0
2686 return nullptr; 0
2687 } ----
2688 } ----
2689 ----
2690 Constant *ConstantExpr::getBinOpAbsorber(unsigned Opcode, Type *Ty) { 0
2691 switch (Opcode) { 0
2692 default: 0
2693 // Doesn't have an absorber. ----
2694 return nullptr; 0
2695 ----
2696 case Instruction::Or: 0
2697 return Constant::getAllOnesValue(Ty); 0
2698 ----
2699 case Instruction::And: 0
2700 case Instruction::Mul: ----
2701 return Constant::getNullValue(Ty); 0
2702 } ----
2703 } ----

2714 GetElementPtrConstantExpr::GetElementPtrConstantExpr( 0
2715 Type *SrcElementTy, Constant *C, ArrayRef IdxList, Type *DestTy) ----
2716 : ConstantExpr(DestTy, Instruction::GetElementPtr, ----
2717 OperandTraits::op_end(this) - 0
2718 (IdxList.size() + 1), 0
2719 IdxList.size() + 1), 0
2720 SrcElementTy(SrcElementTy), 0
2721 ResElementTy(GetElementPtrInst::getIndexedType(SrcElementTy, IdxList)) { 0

2726 } 0

2748 ----
2749 bool ConstantDataSequential::isElementTypeCompatible(Type *Ty) { 0
2750 if (Ty->isHalfTy() || Ty->isBFloatTy() || Ty->isFloatTy() || Ty->isDoubleTy()) 0
2751 return true; 0
2752 if (auto *IT = dyn_cast(Ty)) { 0
2753 switch (IT->getBitWidth()) { 0
2754 case 8: 0
2755 case 16: ----
2756 case 32: ----
2757 case 64: ----
2758 return true; 0
2759 default: break; 0
2760 } ----
2761 } ----
2762 return false; 0
2763 } ----

2776 /// Return the start of the specified element. ----
2777 const char *ConstantDataSequential::getElementPointer(unsigned Elt) const { 0
2778 assert(Elt < getNumElements() && "Invalid Elt"); 0
2779 return DataElements+Elt*getElementByteSize(); 0
2780 } ----
2781 ----
2782 ----
2783 /// Return true if the array is empty or all zeros. ----
2784 static bool isAllZeros(StringRef Arr) { 0
2785 for (char I : Arr) 0
2786 if (I != 0) 0
2787 return false; 0
2788 return true; 0
2789 } ----
2790 ----
2791 /// This is the underlying implementation of all of the ----
2792 /// ConstantDataSequential::get methods. They all thunk down to here, providing ----
2793 /// the correct element type. We take the bytes in as a StringRef because ----
2794 /// we *want* an underlying "char*" to avoid TBAA type punning violations. ----
2795 Constant *ConstantDataSequential::getImpl(StringRef Elements, Type *Ty) { 0
2796 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
2797 if (ArrayType *ATy = dyn_cast(Ty)) 0
2798 assert(isElementTypeCompatible(ATy->getElementType())); 0
2799 else ----
2800 assert(isElementTypeCompatible(cast(Ty)->getElementType())); 0
2801 #endif ----
2802 // If the elements are all zero or there are no elements, return a CAZ, which ----
2803 // is more dense and canonical. ----
2804 if (isAllZeros(Elements)) 0
2805 return ConstantAggregateZero::get(Ty); 0
2806 ----
2807 // Do a lookup to see if we have already formed one of these. ----
2808 auto &Slot = ----
2809 *Ty->getContext() 0
2810 .pImpl->CDSConstants.insert(std::make_pair(Elements, nullptr)) 0
2811 .first; 0
2812 ----
2813 // The bucket can point to a linked list of different CDS's that have the same ----
2814 // body but different types. For example, 0,0,0,1 could be a 4 element array ----
2815 // of i8, or a 1-element array of i32. They'll both end up in the same ----
2816 /// StringMap bucket, linked up by their Next pointers. Walk the list. ----
2817 std::unique_ptr *Entry = &Slot.second; 0
2818 for (; *Entry; Entry = &(*Entry)->Next) 0
2819 if ((*Entry)->getType() == Ty) 0
2820 return Entry->get(); 0
2821 ----
2822 // Okay, we didn't get a hit. Create a node of the right class, link it in, ----
2823 // and return it. ----
2824 if (isa(Ty)) { 0
2825 // Use reset because std::make_unique can't access the constructor. ----
2826 Entry->reset(new ConstantDataArray(Ty, Slot.first().data())); 0
2827 return Entry->get(); 0
2828 } ----
2829 ----
2830 assert(isa(Ty)); 0
2831 // Use reset because std::make_unique can't access the constructor. ----
2832 Entry->reset(new ConstantDataVector(Ty, Slot.first().data())); 0
2833 return Entry->get(); 0
2834 } ----
2835 ----
2836 void ConstantDataSequential::destroyConstantImpl() { 0
2837 // Remove the constant from the StringMap. ----
2838 StringMap> &CDSConstants = ----
2839 getType()->getContext().pImpl->CDSConstants; 0
2840 ----
2841 auto Slot = CDSConstants.find(getRawDataValues()); 0
2842 ----
2843 assert(Slot != CDSConstants.end() && "CDS not found in uniquing table"); 0
2844 ----
2845 std::unique_ptr *Entry = &Slot->getValue(); 0
2846 ----
2847 // Remove the entry from the hash table. ----
2848 if (!(*Entry)->Next) { 0
2849 // If there is only one value in the bucket (common case) it must be this ----
2850 // entry, and removing the entry should remove the bucket completely. ----
2851 assert(Entry->get() == this && "Hash mismatch in ConstantDataSequential"); 0
2852 getContext().pImpl->CDSConstants.erase(Slot); 0
2853 return; 0
2854 } ----
2855 ----
2856 // Otherwise, there are multiple entries linked off the bucket, unlink the ----
2857 // node we care about but keep the bucket around. ----
2858 while (true) { ----
2859 std::unique_ptr &Node = *Entry; 0
2860 assert(Node && "Didn't find entry in its uniquing hash table!"); 0
2861 // If we found our entry, unlink it from the list and we're done. ----
2862 if (Node.get() == this) { 0
2863 Node = std::move(Node->Next); 0
2864 return; 0
2865 } ----
2866 ----
2867 Entry = &Node->Next; 0
2868 } 0
2869 } ----
2870 ----
2871 /// getFP() constructors - Return a constant of array type with a float ----
2872 /// element type taken from argument `ElementType', and count taken from ----
2873 /// argument `Elts'. The amount of bits of the contained type must match the ----
2874 /// number of bits of the type contained in the passed in ArrayRef. ----
2875 /// (i.e. half or bfloat for 16bits, float for 32bits, double for 64bits) Note ----
2876 /// that this can return a ConstantAggregateZero object. ----
2877 Constant *ConstantDataArray::getFP(Type *ElementType, ArrayRef Elts) { 0
2878 assert((ElementType->isHalfTy() || ElementType->isBFloatTy()) && 0
2879 "Element type is not a 16-bit float type"); ----
2880 Type *Ty = ArrayType::get(ElementType, Elts.size()); 0
2881 const char *Data = reinterpret_cast(Elts.data()); 0
2882 return getImpl(StringRef(Data, Elts.size() * 2), Ty); 0
2883 } ----
2884 Constant *ConstantDataArray::getFP(Type *ElementType, ArrayRef Elts) { 0
2885 assert(ElementType->isFloatTy() && "Element type is not a 32-bit float type"); 0
2886 Type *Ty = ArrayType::get(ElementType, Elts.size()); 0
2887 const char *Data = reinterpret_cast(Elts.data()); 0
2888 return getImpl(StringRef(Data, Elts.size() * 4), Ty); 0
2889 } ----
2890 Constant *ConstantDataArray::getFP(Type *ElementType, ArrayRef Elts) { 0
2891 assert(ElementType->isDoubleTy() && 0
2892 "Element type is not a 64-bit float type"); ----
2893 Type *Ty = ArrayType::get(ElementType, Elts.size()); 0
2894 const char *Data = reinterpret_cast(Elts.data()); 0
2895 return getImpl(StringRef(Data, Elts.size() * 8), Ty); 0
2896 } ----
2897 ----
2898 Constant *ConstantDataArray::getString(LLVMContext &Context, 0
2899 StringRef Str, bool AddNull) { ----
2900 if (!AddNull) { 0
2901 const uint8_t *Data = Str.bytes_begin(); 0
2902 return get(Context, ArrayRef(Data, Str.size())); 0
2903 } ----
2904 ----
2905 SmallVector ElementVals; 0
2906 ElementVals.append(Str.begin(), Str.end()); 0
2907 ElementVals.push_back(0); 0
2908 return get(Context, ElementVals); 0
2909 } 0
2910 ----
2911 /// get() constructors - Return a constant with vector type with an element ----
2912 /// count and element type matching the ArrayRef passed in. Note that this ----
2913 /// can return a ConstantAggregateZero object. ----
2914 Constant *ConstantDataVector::get(LLVMContext &Context, ArrayRef Elts){ 0
2915 auto *Ty = FixedVectorType::get(Type::getInt8Ty(Context), Elts.size()); 0
2916 const char *Data = reinterpret_cast(Elts.data()); 0
2917 return getImpl(StringRef(Data, Elts.size() * 1), Ty); 0

3156 ----
3157 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
3158 // handleOperandChange implementations ----
3159 ----
3160 /// Update this constant array to change uses of ----
3161 /// 'From' to be uses of 'To'. This must update the uniquing data structures ----
3162 /// etc. ----
3163 /// ----
3164 /// Note that we intentionally replace all uses of From with To here. Consider ----
3165 /// a large array that uses 'From' 1000 times. By handling this case all here, ----
3166 /// ConstantArray::handleOperandChange is only invoked once, and that ----
3167 /// single invocation handles all 1000 uses. Handling them one at a time would ----
3168 /// work, but would be really slow because it would have to unique each updated ----
3169 /// array instance. ----
3170 /// ----
3171 void Constant::handleOperandChange(Value *From, Value *To) { 0
3172 Value *Replacement = nullptr; 0
3173 switch (getValueID()) { 0
3174 default: 0
3175 llvm_unreachable("Not a constant!"); 0
3176 #define HANDLE_CONSTANT(Name) \ ----
3177 case Value::Name##Val: \ ----
3178 Replacement = cast(this)->handleOperandChangeImpl(From, To); \ ----
3179 break; ----
3180 #include "llvm/IR/Value.def" ----
3181 } ----
3182 ----
3183 // If handleOperandChangeImpl returned nullptr, then it handled ----
3184 // replacing itself and we don't want to delete or replace anything else here. ----
3185 if (!Replacement) 0
3186 return; 0
3187 ----
3188 // I do need to replace this with an existing value. ----
3189 assert(Replacement != this && "I didn't contain From!"); 0
3190 ----
3191 // Everyone using this now uses the replacement. ----
3192 replaceAllUsesWith(Replacement); 0
3193 ----
3194 // Delete the old constant! ----
3195 destroyConstant(); 0
3196 } ----
3197 ----
3198 Value *ConstantArray::handleOperandChangeImpl(Value *From, Value *To) { 0
3199 assert(isa(To) && "Cannot make Constant refer to non-constant!"); 0
3200 Constant *ToC = cast(To); 0
3201 ----
3202 SmallVector Values; 0
3203 Values.reserve(getNumOperands()); // Build replacement array. 0
3204 ----
3205 // Fill values with the modified operands of the constant array. Also, ----
3206 // compute whether this turns into an all-zeros array. ----
3207 unsigned NumUpdated = 0; 0
3208 ----
3209 // Keep track of whether all the values in the array are "ToC". ----
3210 bool AllSame = true; 0
3211 Use *OperandList = getOperandList(); 0
3212 unsigned OperandNo = 0; 0
3213 for (Use *O = OperandList, *E = OperandList+getNumOperands(); O != E; ++O) { 0
3214 Constant *Val = cast(O->get()); 0
3215 if (Val == From) { 0
3216 OperandNo = (O - OperandList); 0
3217 Val = ToC; 0
3218 ++NumUpdated; 0
3219 } ----
3220 Values.push_back(Val); 0
3221 AllSame &= Val == ToC; 0
3222 } ----
3223 ----
3224 if (AllSame && ToC->isNullValue()) 0
3225 return ConstantAggregateZero::get(getType()); 0
3226 ----
3227 if (AllSame && isa(ToC)) 0
3228 return UndefValue::get(getType()); 0
3229 ----
3230 // Check for any other type of constant-folding. ----
3231 if (Constant *C = getImpl(getType(), Values)) 0
3232 return C; 0
3233 ----
3234 // Update to the new value. ----
3235 return getContext().pImpl->ArrayConstants.replaceOperandsInPlace( 0
3236 Values, this, From, ToC, NumUpdated, OperandNo); 0
3237 } 0
